  "notes": "The L59 is mechanically identical to the LM7 5.3L iron-block Gen III LS but calibrated for E85/flex-fuel operation. Uses the same 96mm bore, 92mm stroke, 9.5:1 compression, and cathedral-port aluminum heads. The ECM and injectors are sized for flex-fuel, making it a notable swap candidate for builds targeting E85 compatibility from the factory tune. Swappers typically re-tune regardless, so the flex-fuel hardware is a bonus. Uses 24x reluctor wheel. Oil pan swap required for most car chassis. Frequently misidentified as LM7 in salvage yards.",
